(71, 'Cat5e sheilded outdoor network cable (black)', 'This Cat 5e outdoor Shielded twisted pair ( stp ) uv jacket cable with messenger is a high performance data communication cable suitable for 350mhz high speed data applications, gigabit ethernet, fast ethernet and 155Mbps TP-PMD/CDDI. It has excellent attenuation and crosstalk characteristics and exceeds TIA/EIA-568-C.2 specification. With its uv resistant jacket, this ethernet cable is designed for outdoor installations where resistance to sun rays is important.It is also equipped with galvanized steel messenger to support the cable in aerial installations. This cable is verified by ETL to be type CMX. The wires are 24 awg in size and are made of solid bare ( pure ) copper conductors. All 4 pairs are easily identified by color stripes. The insulation material is PE and the jacket material is LLDPE and the cable is equipped with AL foil as a shield with drain wire. This cable is supplied in 1000 feet wooden spool and sequential length markings are printed on the jacket.', NULL, NULL, 'Cat5e Sheilded Outdoor (black) - 1ft.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(72, 'Cat5e sheilded cable ends (100 pcs.)', 'These connectors are commonly used for making ethernet patch cables using shielded stranded Category 5 Enhanced ethernet cabling.  Stranded bulk cabling is the most popular cabling used for patch cables as it provides the most flexibility, whereas solid cable is normally reserved for network runs from the patch panel to the wall plate.', NULL, NULL, 'Cat5e Sheilded Ends (100 pcs.)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
